      <acttitle>Land Surveyors Act</acttitle>
      <title>Form of Oath Regulation</title>
      <content>
        <section toc="false">
          <marginalnote>Form of oath</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>1</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>An oath under section 46 (1) of the Land Surveyors Act must be in the following form:</sectiontext>
          <indent1>I, ...................., swear/affirm that</indent1>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>a</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>I am a Canadian citizen or permanent resident of Canada, and</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>b</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>I will faithfully and without partiality perform my duties as a land surveyor and member of the Corporation of Land Surveyors of British Columbia according to law.</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
        </section>
        <provisionsnote>[Provisions of the <actname>Land Surveyors Act</actname>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 248, relevant to the enactment of this regulation: section 46 (1)]</provisionsnote>
      </content>
    </reg>
